  "description": "A use-after-free flaw was found in the Linux kernel's netfilter: nf_tables component which can be exploited to achieve local privilege escalation. On an error when building a nftables rule, deactivating immediate expressions in nft_immediate_deactivate() can unbind the chain and objects to be deactivated but used later.",
